data.title: Super cool place
data.text: great food and a lot of it.. Chippiotle like just better.. Feels indy owned. hope it is.. ill go here when im in akron. so much food and great prices.. super rad staff!

data.title: Don't waste your time
data.text: Stopped in for a quick bite to eat before a baseball game.  This place could best be described as a Chipotle knockoff, but it does nothing as well as Chipotle.  The quality is not as good, it is more expensive, and the service was poor.  My experience was so poor, I will not give it a 2nd chance.

data.title: Not Much To Knock About This Chipotle Knock-Off
data.text: This place is like a Chipotle knock-off. With that said, the burrito I had was tasty, large and filling. It tasted like it was made from fresh ingredients. I also tasted my wife's burrito bowl and it was good also. We had disco fries and shared them as a side. They were good as well. Air conditioning would have been nice. Just because you serve Mexican cuisine doesn't mean it needs to feel as if you are in Mexico. I really felt bad for the workers who had to work in those conditions. Akron is an economically depressed city and I can understand why pennies need to be cut to turn a profit. My wife and I would eat here again if we were going to a show at the lock or Akron Civic Theater.

data.title: Very small portion fish tacos, good fries
data.text: Had we not ordered the delicious disco fries I would have left hungry.  Two 3" street tacos, one 4" fish taco, fries and two beers ran $28 before tip.  Good food but the single fish taco was a small portion for $7.

data.title: Great little joint...simple and delicious
data.text: El Gato is a great addition to downtown akron. It's  simple and easy food but tasty. The street tacos are true to the real thing. (As in simple and small). They have a great  selection  of Mexican sodas and beer. Tasty, inexpensive  and quick. Great lunch spot.
